A lawyer and politician, Edward Moore Kennedy was born on the 22nd of February 1932 in Boston, Massachusetts, United States. He is perhaps best known to the world as former United States Senator from Massachusetts, where he served for 47 years. He was the youngest son of Joseph P. Kennedy and the youngest brother of President John F. Kennedy. He was also the youngest son of Joseph P. Kennedy. In the course of his career, he worked from 1962 until his death in 2009.
